hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Potential terms on the axis (Î¸=0, r=z):  
   $$\Phi_Q(z)=-G\,\frac{Q\,P_2(1)}{z^3}=-G\,\frac{Q}{z^3},\quad 
     \Phi_O(z)=-G\,\frac{O\,P_3(1)}{z^4}=-G\,\frac{O}{z^4}.$$

2. Tidal tensor component:  
   $$T_{zz}=\frac{d^2\Phi}{dz^2}.$$

3. Quadrupole contribution:  
   $$\frac{d\Phi_Q}{dz}=-GQ\frac{d}{dz}(z^{-3})=3GQ\,z^{-4},$$  
   $$\frac{d^2\Phi_Q}{dz^2}=3GQ\frac{d}{dz}(z^{-4})=-12GQ\,z^{-5} 
     \;\Rightarrow\; |(T_{zz})_Q|=12G\frac{|Q|}{z^5}.$$

4. Octupole contribution:  
   $$\frac{d\Phi_O}{dz}=-GO\frac{d}{dz}(z^{-4})=4GO\,z^{-5},$$  
   $$\frac{d^2\Phi_O}{dz^2}=4GO\frac{d}{dz}(z^{-5})=-20GO\,z^{-6} 
     \;\Rightarrow\; |(T_{zz})_O|=20G\frac{|O|}{z^6}.$$

5. Ratio of magnitudes:  
   $$\mathcal{R}
     =\frac{|(T_{zz})_O|}{|(T_{zz})_Q|}
     =\frac{20G\,|O|\,z^{-6}}{12G\,|Q|\,z^{-5}}
     =\frac{20}{12}\,\frac{|O|}{|Q|}\,\frac1{z}
     =\frac{5}{3}\,\frac{|O|}{|Q|\,z}.$$
